    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/399.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1780.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 20, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to previous
                    correspondence regarding the negotiation of a convention concerning the Colorado
                    River, <pb facs="1096" n="992" xml:id="pg_992"/> and especially to the
                    Department’s instruction No. 974, of September 10th, and the Ambassador’s
                    despatch No. 1690, of the 26th of the same month.</p>
                <p>In this connection I beg to transmit herewith copies of the Ambassador’s
                        note<note n="1" xml:id="d1291fn1">Not printed.</note> to the Minister for
                    .Foreign Affairs, dated September 21; translations of the Minister’s note<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d1291fn2">Not printed.</note> to me of November 16; and copies
                    and translations of the counter draft<note n="1" xml:id="d1291fn3">Not
                        printed.</note> of the conversion enclosed with the latter note.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Montgomery Schuyler</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
